<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-12-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-12-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="681" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d681">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Olney</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Terrell</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-12-16"><hi rend="italic">December 16,
                                    1895</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Your 697 received. In the event of conflict at Zeitoun you should ask
                            effective protection of American property there, as well as for any
                            American citizens remaining. Renew efforts to keep open communication
                            with citizens at Marash and other exposed points.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Olney.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>